<HEADLINE>
<P>
JACK HANNAH; DIRECTED DONALD DUCK CARTOONS FOR DISNEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jack Hannah, 81, animator and director of more than 100 Donald Duck cartoons. 
A native of Nogales, Ariz., Hannah moved to Los Angeles to study art.He joined 
the Walt Disney Productions animation staff in 1933, working on early Mickey 
Mouse and Silly Symphony cartoons, as well as on Donald Duck cartoons. He was 
credited as one animator of Disney's Academy Award-winning "The Old Mill." 
After briefly working on stories, Hannah moved into directing, handling the 
antics of Donald Duck and 14 one-hour Disney television programs. He retired 
from Disney in 1959 but continued to work occasionally for Disney and for 
Walter Lantz. Hannah developed the School of Character Animation at CalArts and 
taught there for eight years. He was also an oil painter, principally of 
landscapes, which he exhibited in several galleries. On June 11 in Burbank of 
cancer. 
</P>
