<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; 1 IN GROUP OF 7 STABS YOUTH IN HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG HERNANDEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A group of seven teen-agers followed a 17-year-old into his home, and one 
person in the group stabbed him in the chest with a small knife, police said 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Family members told police that the victim, Fredy Urquiza, walked out of his 
family's house in the 200 block of North Figueroa Street about 9:25 p.m. They 
said that the teen-ager turned around almost immediately and walked back, 
followed by the group, said Sgt. Dick Faust. 
</P>
<P>
 "It appears that one person is responsible for the stabbing, even though he 
was accompanied by six other people," Faust said. 
</P>
<P>
 After the stabbing, the group ran. They remain at large, and no arrests have 
been made. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim's parents and a brother, who were at home when the stabbing 
occurred, took him to the hospital. His condition was not released. 
</P>
<P>
 Police have not yet established a motive for the stabbing. The knife has not 
been found, Faust said. GREG HERNANDEZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
