<HEADLINE>
<P>
STERN'S TERMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It was fun listening to Claudia Puig's attempt to interview Howard Stern. Her 
resulting story was just what Stern wanted. The only thing she left out was his 
not realizing that she writes for the Los Angeles Times. 
</P>
<P>
 It may be self-proclaimed, but Stern definitely seems to have the media as 
"his audience." It's amazing how many journalists are willing to accept his 
wrath by doing interviews "on his terms." You can't tell me The Times didn't 
get what it expected. 
</P>
<P>
 Then, the "Howard hype" gets front-page Calendar coverage ("Move Over, 
Woodward & Bernstein," June 2). I personally enjoyed the story, but wouldn't a 
feature on ABC's "Jacqui's Dilemma" (reviewed on F9), exploring teen-age 
pregnancy, have had more relevance? 
</P>
<P>
 FRANK H. LIEBERMAN 
</P>
<P>
 Katie Face Productions 
</P>
<P>
 Culver City 
</P>
