<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE & OUT; NITTY-GRITTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times-Post News Service 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * To clean a stained teapot, fill with water and 1/4 cup bleach; let sit; 
rinse thoroughly before using. 
</P>
<P>
 * To loosen a rusted bolt easily, pour a few drops of carbonated soft drink 
onto the rusted nail or bolt.The acid in the soda will break up some of the 
rust. 
</P>
<P>
 * Clean walls with a solution of one quart warm water and two tablespoons 
vinegar. Rinse well and dry. 
</P>
<P>
 * Shine chrome fixtures with a soft cloth dampened with cider vinegar. 
</P>
<P>
 * To keep the house smelling fresh, pour a few drops of wintergreen oil 
(purchased at drugstores) onto a cotton ball and place in a glass container. 
The smell will last for several weeks and can be replenished easily when it 
fades. 
</P>
<P>
 * Use an old blender with a glass bowl to mix latex paint thoroughly. When 
finished, clean glass container with hot water and a small amount of dish 
detergent and whisk clean by turning on the appliance. 
</P>
<P>
 * Tips for the gardeners: Try using an apple corer to dig up garden weeds; a 
hot-water bottle filled partially with water can provide a cushion for knees, 
curtain rods are a sturdy support for vines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
