<P>
DISCOVERIES: INSIDE & OUT; FLASHBACK, FAST FORWARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CYNDI Y. NIGHTENGALE, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 These chairs don't take a back seat to anyone. 
</P>
<P>
 Thayer Coggin, the High Point, N.C.-based furniture manufacturer, produces 
dramatic creations of yesteryear as well as those with a futuristic lilt. 
</P>
<P>
 A wing chair (about $1,300), part of the '50s Retro Collection, has scaled 
down "wings," flared arms and a loose seat cushion for comfort. 
</P>
<P>
 The 12-piece retro collection, designed by Milo Baughman, captures the grace 
and humor of the past and melds it with the technology of today. 
</P>
<P>
 With its bold curves, double stitching and tapered legs, the Envoy chair 
(about $1,600) is a fit for many contemporary homes. 
</P>
<P>
 The chairs can be purchased in Orange County at Moda Italia, 18582 Beach 
Blvd., Huntington Beach, or direct from Thayer Coggin, (910) 841-6000. Just for 
Kicks 
</P>
<P>
 World Cup soccer is here at last, and, hoping the event is one people will 
