<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: MOORPARK; MAN FOUND GUILTY OF MOLESTING GIRL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Ventura County jury has convicted a 22-year-old Moorpark man of four counts 
of child molestation on charges that he sexually attacked a 12-year-old girl on 
her way home from Chaparral Middle School. 
</P>
<P>
 Robert Magdaleno, who said the girl willingly had sex with him, faces up to 34 
years in prison. 
</P>
<P>
 The jury in the courtroom of Superior Court Judge Allan Steele acquitted 
Magdaleno of a fifth count of child molestation in its decision Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The girl, who testified during the trial, accused the defendant of taking her 
to an unoccupied home and attacking her on Nov. 1. 
</P>
<P>
 Magdaleno was arrested several hours after the incident when the girl 
identified him in a photo lineup. 
</P>
<P>
 During the trial, Deputy Dist. Atty. Rebecca L. Day told the jury that the 
girl was a virgin prior to the assault and that she told Magdaleno she did not 
want to have sex with him. 
</P>
<P>
 Defense attorney Joe Lax said the girl consented to the sex, but accused 
Magdaleno of using force against her because she was late arriving home that 
day. DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
