<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; REWARD OFFERED IN MARTIAL ARTS 
ROBBERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County Crime Stoppers is offering a reward for information about a 
Thousand Oaks burglary in which someone kicked open the door of a martial arts 
store and stole $13,500 worth of computer equipment and clothing. 
</P>
<P>
 During the nights of June 8 or 9, someone broke into Dragon Books, a 
publishing company that specializes in martial arts books, clothing and 
training equipment, and stole an Apple computer, software and other equipment, 
said Sgt. Kitty Hoberg of the Ventura County Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspect also took a box of black Okinawan karate belts, which have red 
Japanese characters on them. 
</P>
<P>
 Crime Stoppers is offering up to $1,000 for information that helps solve the 
burglary, officials said. Anyone with information about the location of the 
belts or computer equipment should call 494-TALK. 
</P>
<P>
 Callers may remain anonymous and will be assigned an identification number. If 
the information leads to an arrest with a criminal complaint filed, the caller 
will be eligible for a reward. TRACY WILSON 
