<P>
VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: BUSINESS QUAKE-LOAN COUNSELING OFFERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Has your small business been turned down for a federal disaster loan? Haven't 
even figured out how to apply for it? 
</P>
<P>
 The Valley Economic Development Center, through funds provided by the city of 
Los Angeles, is offering "Hospitals for Businesses," free one-on-one counseling 
for business owners on how to get those loans. 
</P>
<P>
 According to a news release sent out by the center, about half the requests 
for federal disaster loans have been rejected and only a quarter of the 
applications that were sent have been returned. 
</P>
<P>
 The counseling sessions will be held in three locations in the San Fernando 
Valley: 14541 Victory Blvd., Van Nuys; Chatsworth Chamber of Commerce office, 
21943 Plummer St., Chatsworth, and 19040 Vanowen St., Reseda. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the center at (818) 989-4377. MAKI BECKER 
