<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CAMARILLO; CHAMBER PANEL PICKS 10 NEW MEMBERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J.E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ten new members have been elected to the Camarillo Chamber of Commerce's board 
of directors. 
</P>
<P>
 Elected were Gary Cushing, president of GSMC, Inc.; Kirk Davis, former 
publisher of the Oxnard Press Courier; Susan Duxbury, Camarillo Community Bank 
loan officer; Roy Hales, president of Hales Engineering; Michael Horton, owner 
of Michael Horton & Associates; and Carol Larson, Southern California Edison 
area manager. 
</P>
<P>
 Also elected to the board were Mark J. Munro, president of Voice-Tel of 
Southern California; Charles Padilla, vice president of St. John's Pleasant 
Valley Hospital; Anne Tromba, co-owner of Giovanni's Restaurant; and Toni 
Weitzel, owner of Best of Everything. 
</P>
<P>
 The 10 will be installed during the chamber's annual awards dinner June 24 at 
Las Posas Country Club. J.E. MITCHELL 
