<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: HEALTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 FHP Completes TakeCare Merger: FHP International, a Fountain Valley 
managed-care company, said it has completed its $1.1-billion acquisition of 
TakeCare Inc., creating the fifth-largest health maintenance organization in 
the United States. FHP also announced a reorganization that divides the company 
into three operating divisions.The company named Dr. Ryan Trimble, an FHP 
senior vice president, president of its health care delivery division, which 
will operate FHP medical and dental centers, hospitals, pharmacies and 
laboratories. R. Judd Jessup, former president of TakeCare, was named president 
of the health plans division, which oversees contracting with independent and 
FHP medical groups. And Burke Gumbiner, formerly FHP's senior vice president of 
marketing and sales, will head the company's indemnity life and health 
insurance and workers' compensation companies. 
</P>
