<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; TODAY AT A GLANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LISA DILLMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 GROUP A 
</P>
<P>
 at Rose Bowl 
</P>
<P>
 Colombia vs. Romania 
</P>
<P>
 * TIME: 4:30 p.m. PDT. 
</P>
<P>
 * TV: ESPN, Univision. 
</P>
<P>
 * KEY MATCHUPS: Colombia has been picked by Pele as the favorite in the 
tournament and plays a wide-open style that was favored by Brazil during Pele's 
era.The game will turn on how well Romanian defenders handle the multifaceted 
Colombian offense with the best playmaker in the world, Carlos Valderrama, 
trying to set up forward Faustino Asprilla and midfielder Freddy Rincon. 
Romania could be hurt by its overdependence on spectacular midfielder Gheorghe 
Hagi. 
</P>
<P>
 * OUTLOOK: Unlike the other venues, the weather in Pasadena is not expected to 
have an impact on the game. The game will start late in the afternoon and the 
weather service is predicting temperatures around 65-68 degrees under partly 
cloudy skies. It could be an explosive match. Romanian Coach Anghel Iordanescu 
said he expects to reach the semifinals. Said Colombian Coach Francisco 
Maturana: "I think we have the technical ability and mind set to make it to the 
finals." 
</P>
<P>
 * OUTCOME: Colombia, 2-1. And maybe if the crowd is lucky -- at least one 
cartwheel by Asprilla, a personal tradition after he scores. LISA DILLMAN 
</P>
