<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIRM GETS LICENSE TO RUN HOLLYWOOD PARK CASINO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The California Attorney General's office has granted a license to Pacific 
Casino Management, Inc., the company Hollywood Park has contracted to operate 
its casino, which will probably open in the first week of July. 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific Casino Management, Inc., a newly formed corporation headed by Don 
Klosterman and Eddie LeBaron, will pay Hollywood Park a lease fee. 
</P>
<P>
 "Opening the only, truly world-class casino card club in Los Angeles has 
involved extensive planning and hard work; we are delighted to be nearing the 
day when we will see these efforts reach fruition," said R.D. Hubbard, 
Hollywood Park chairman and CEO. "Aesthetically, the casino has exceeded our 
greatest expectations, and we are confident Los Angeles will be pleased with 
its new casino." BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
