<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOLF AND PARQUE WILL BE PITCHING UNDER THE GUN IN ALL-STAR GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF FLETCHER, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For left-handers Randy Wolf and Jim Parque, the added significance of this 
year's Bernie Milligan high school all-star baseball game might be found 
somewhere behind home plate, carrying a radar gun. 
</P>
<P>
 That would be Terry Reynolds, the Dodgers' scouting director, who is expected 
to watch El Camino Real's Wolf and Crescenta Valley's Parque, the starting 
pitchers at the 18th annual game that starts today at 3:30 p.m. at Cal State 
Northridge. Both pitchers were selected by the Dodgers in the draft earlier 
this month. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm not really (nervous)," Parque said. "I'll just go out there and do my 
job. Even if I screw up, he'll see that I can do something." 
</P>
<P>
 There will be no shame for Parque (12-3, 0.49 earned-run average this season) 
or Wolf (12-3, 1.19) if they are less than perfect today. Parque is a member of 
East team, Wolf the West. They will face lineups drawn from the top seniors 
from Glendale to the Antelope Valley to Newbury Park. 
</P>
<P>
 The East team includes 10 players who batted .400 or better, led by Burbank's 
Brian Sindle (.540) and Hoover's Ron Pirayoff (.500). 
</P>
<P>
 Also on the team are Notre Dame's Justin Bunch (.479), Antelope Valley's Chris 
Tapia (.467, 43 runs batted in), Palmdale's Jerome Payton (.462, 37 stolen 
bases), Sylmar's Art Diaz (.447), Highland's Casey Cheshier (.438), Saugus' 
Danny Cato (.436), Poly's Sam Vizcarra (.425) and Montclair Prep's Matt Muler 
(.417). 
</P>
<P>
 The West's top hitters are Chatsworth shortstop Bryan LaCour (.481, 41 RBIs) 
and Simi Valley third baseman Ryan Hankins (.483, nine home runs). 
</P>
<P>
 Calabasas' Josh Morton (.475), Reseda's Carlos Nunez (.463, seven home runs), 
Royal's Joel Mellinger (.451), and Moorpark's Jason Adamson (.435) and Rick 
Collier (.407) also play for the West. 
</P>
<P>
 Besides Parque, the East's pitching staff includes Palmdale's David Glick 
(11-3, 1.38), Notre Dame's Rich Igou (11-2, 1.43) and Sylmar's Carlos Velazco 
(11-3, 1.80). 
</P>
<P>
 Other West pitchers includes Wolf, Newbury Park's Ray Clinton (10-3, 1.41), 
Chatsworth's Jim DeBiase (10-1, 2.44) and L.A. Baptist's Matt Hernandez (9-2, 
1.47). 
</P>
<P>
 The East team will be coached by Notre Dame's Tom Dill and Poly's Chuck 
Schwal, and the West by Chatsworth's Tom Meusborn and L.A. Baptist's Mark 
Bates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
