<HEADLINE>
<P>
GAYHART LEADS FROM START TO FINISH FOR FIRST VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DARIN ESPER, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Malibu's Adail Gayhart went wire-to-wire in winning the 20-lap Street Stock 
feature Friday night at Ventura Raceway. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the first victory of the season for Gayhart, who came into the race 
seventh in the points standings. 
</P>
<P>
 Defending champion Paul Moore of Oak View, the series leader, spent most of 
the race running 10 lengths behind Gayhart in second place, before mounting a 
late challenge on lap 18. 
</P>
<P>
 But Moore's challenge fell short, as Ventura's Randy McGraw, a two-time 
winner, slipped around Moore in Turn 2 on the last lap and held on for second. 
</P>
<P>
 Bill Bartels of Marina del Rey, who ran second for the first five laps and 
helped Moore pressure Gayhart for most of the race, finished fourth. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Maria's Ryan Cole added to his points lead in the IMCA Modified class by 
winning his fourth 15-lap Main event victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura's Doug Thornton finished second despite a first-lap collision with 
Santa Maria's Bill Lauer that spun Thornton in turn one, bringing on a caution 
flag and forcing Thornton to start from the back of the pack. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura's Gary Howard won the 15-lap IMCA Sprint Main. 
</P>
<P>
 Bruce Dunson of Ventura won his fourth 15-lap Mini Stock Main Event. 
</P>
