<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: A SOFTBALL ALL-AMERICAN, JONES CONSIDERS BASKETBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE HISERMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Shannon Jones has completed her senior softball season for Cal State 
Northridge, but her college athletic career might not be over. 
</P>
<P>
 Jones, an All-American third baseman, said Friday that she is considering 
trying out for the Northridge basketball team.She would have one season of NCAA 
Division I eligibility. 
</P>
<P>
 Jones, who is 5-foot-10, last played competitive basketball at Mira Loma High 
in Sacramento, where she was an All-City forward. 
</P>
<P>
 At Northridge, she played on a championship intramural basketball team along 
with two other Northridge softball players. 
</P>
<P>
 A business major who is roughly a year short of earning her degree, Jones will 
consider all options before making a decision. 
</P>
<P>
 "Playing basketball would make it tougher on me academically, but I would also 
like to enjoy my final year athletically," Jones said. MIKE HISERMAN 
</P>
