<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE NOTES / STEVE KRESAL; CARLSON, KAZMER, LEE NAMED ATHLETES OF 
YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fullerton's Kevin Carlson, Orange Coast's LeAnn Kazmer and Golden West's 
Jessica Lee were selected Orange County community college athletes of the year 
by area sports information directors. 
</P>
<P>
 Carlson, from Katella High, was a standout basketball player and high jumper 
for the Hornets. Carlson, who is 6 feet 5, averaged 16 points for Fullerton and 
was selected to the All-Orange Empire Conference basketball team. 
</P>
<P>
 With no time off, he went right from basketball to the high jump. Carlson won 
the State title with a jump of 7- 1/4. He is going to Southern California 
College next fall and will compete in basketball and track and field. 
</P>
<P>
 Kazmer, from Arrowhead (Wis.) High, was a standout forward for the Orange 
Coast women's basketball team. She and Cypress' Sara Works were named most 
valuable players of the Orange Empire Conference. Kazmer also was an all-State 
selection. 
</P>
<P>
 She helped Orange Coast reach the semifinal round of the State tournament. 
Kazmer averaged 20 points and 11 rebounds for the Pirates. She accepted a 
scholarship to Las Vegas where she will compete in basketball and track and 
field. 
</P>
<P>
 Lee, from Capistrano Valley High School, was a setter for the Golden West 
women's volleyball team that went 27-0, and won the State title. She was 
selected national player of the year by the American Volleyball Coaches' Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 Lee, who also was selected as MVP of the Orange Empire Conference, will attend 
the University of Illinois next fall. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Coaches of the Year: Golden West's Albert Gasparian (women's volleyball) and 
Orange Coast's Don Watson (swimming) were selected women's coaches of the year 
by the sports information directors. Cypress' Scott Pickler (baseball) was the 
men's coach of the year. 
</P>
<P>
 Gasparian helped Golden West to its third State title in four seasons and has 
an 11-year record of 236-30 with the Rustlers. Watson's team won its sixth 
consecutive State title and the 10th in 11 seasons. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast has won 92 consecutive women's dual meets dating to February, 
1982. 
</P>
<P>
 Pickler guided Cypress to its second State title in the last four seasons. His 
team finished with a Cypress single-season record 43 victories and has a 
301-153 mark after 10 seasons. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Amy Jalewalia, a former standout at La Quinta High and UCLA, will be an 
assistant for the Cypress women's basketball team next fall. Jalewalia helped 
La Quinta to a 1990 Southern Section title. 
</P>
<P>
 Jalewalia will be working for Cypress Coach Kevin Kiernan, who was her coach 
in high school. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA061894-0264 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 052578 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
